WEBVTT

00:08:58.109 --> 00:09:01.188
I have become an advocate
for stay-at-home parents.

00:09:01.502 --> 00:09:02.660
Why?

00:09:02.684 --> 00:09:05.350
Because finally, I was
standing in their shoes.

00:09:05.898 --> 00:09:08.375
Because when you're standing
in someone else's shoes,

00:09:08.399 --> 00:09:10.666
you see the world
from a different perspective.

00:09:10.680 --> 00:09:14.263
And when you start to take steps,
it feels like baby steps, wobbling.

00:09:14.633 --> 00:09:16.823
But then they turn into stomps.

00:09:16.847 --> 00:09:20.183
And you start making footprints
for the next generation to walk in.

00:09:21.085 --> 00:09:23.577
See, we're walking
on a certain path, as parents.

00:09:23.601 --> 00:09:24.910
We're all in this together.

00:09:24.934 --> 00:09:27.840
No one can deny that family
is one of the biggest foundations

00:09:27.864 --> 00:09:29.022
in anyone's life.

00:09:29.046 --> 00:09:30.732
And we're all walking on this path,